x4freetext: The experiment was performed at the
Centre de Recherches du Cyclotron at Louvain-la-Neuve.
Polypropylene target with thickness of 3.5 mu-m.
Scattered protons were detected at
zero degree by a EdE telescope consisting of silicon
detectors located 50 cm downstream of the target,
composed of a 500 mu-m E detector (18 keV FWHM
resolution) and a 6 mm Si(Li) E detector (28 keV
FWHM),which covered a solid angle of 5 msr.
